    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-30T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-30T18:00:00-05:00" n="191"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d191">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>/4–1746:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-30T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 30, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USdel</gloss>. Our instruction on admission to
                    membership in UN of April 17, 1946 authorized you only to initiate discussions
                    with other delegations to determine extent of support for resolution and rules
                    of procedure set forth in instruction. In view of likelihood of early
                    consideration of membership rules in Committee of Experts and possibility that
                    move may suddenly be made to place Albanian application on Provisional Agenda of
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> you are authorized to take action as
                    follows:</p>
                <p>If, in your view, there is sufficient support among members of <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> to assure favorable reception of resolution set
                    forth in instruction of April 17, 1946, you may immediately communicate
                    resolution to Secretary-General for inclusion on Provisional Agenda of <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> meeting. You may also at your discretion
                    introduce in Committee of Experts rules of procedure on admission of members set
                    forth in instruction of April 17, 1946. We still hope, however, that resolution
                    can be introduced in <gloss target="#t_SC2">SC</gloss> before introduction of
                    proposed rules of procedure in Committee of Experts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
